d sediment. This was the beginning to a difficult week waiting for BP to provide clear instructions on how they wanted to proceed with the off spec cargo loaded into 4Ws. The vessel loaded other tanks evenly spread with clean Naphtha and would later commingle all tanks with Naphtha in Houston. After 4-5 days of discussing how to proceed with the off spec Naphtha in 4W, BP finally provided instruction for vessel to decant the water/sediment from the tanks and perform an internal transfer to the ROT. After the decanting \u0026 internal transfer operation, the vessel was shifted into Bolivar Roads for sampling of the remaining cargo in 4W. This was found to be on spec, so vsl proceeded to the Houston berth and commingled in all tanks, including 4W. The deslopping of the ROT was performed alongside the terminal at Charterer\u0027s direction and will be rebilled to them as agreed, along with the shifting cost into Bolivar Roads. \n\n \n\nOnce the off spec cargo was settled, the voyage was very straightforward and seamless discharge. Freight increased due to the additional port included after generation. We had additional time in the load ports partially due to extended time alongside in Beaumont due to the off spec cargo and also due to waiting time in Houston. Days on demurrage totaled $250,000. Port costs increased over all due to the additional port. Overall the bunker consumption was not as high as expected as vessel burned less LSMGO and a little more VLSFO which of course is more cost effective. \n\n \n\nEU ETS was estimated at $29,017 and now that we have the verified EUAs (attached), the total is estimated at $24,069. We are still waiting the final price and will update VMS once finalized."},{"modifiedDate":"2024-05-30T16:29:36.723","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Received Ghent towage. Awaiting agent FDA."},{"modifiedDate":"2024-05-21T13:48:28.3","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Updated Demurrage"},{"modifiedDate":"2024-05-21T12:53:41.197","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Beaumont costs less than expected"},{"modifiedDate":"2024-05-21T12:42:54.553","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"EU ETS Verified MT included. Awaiting final price."},{"modifiedDate":"2024-05-16T14:24:35.717","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Vsl arrived the Ghent earlier than estimated and burned less fuel than VMS expected."},{"modifiedDate":"2024-05-14T17:31:35.517","modifiedByFull":"Butcher, Carol","remark":"Freight updated - increase due to change of disport/flat rate"},{"modifiedDate":"2024-04-29T13:14:30.103","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Extended stay in Hou, but pilot delayed due to traffic. so not as much dem."},{"modifiedDate":"2024-04-19T16:56:47.18","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"added deumurrage since Hou was added."},{"modifiedDate":"2024-04-19T16:53:51.32","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Houston added as load port."},{"modifiedDate":"2024-04-19T13:14:42.837","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Included costs for Bolivar Roads bunkering."},{"modifiedDate":"2024-04-18T14:10:48.31","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Vsl drifted until receiving orders to proceed to Bolivar for bunkering. Bunker barge delayed causing a bit of waiting time in Galveston."},{"modifiedDate":"2024-04-18T14:07:39.573","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"LSMGO bunker prices were generated incorrectly."}],"offhireList":[],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}